<h1>AI Integration and Ollama Server Management</h1>
<p>This document outlines the integration of AI features into the Comserv application, including Ollama server management, auto-startup capabilities, and API endpoints.</p>

<h2>Ollama Server Management</h2>

<h3>Start Server Endpoint</h3>
<p><code>/ai/start_server</code> - Starts the Ollama server when it is not running.</p>
<ul>
    <li><strong>Method:</strong> POST</li>
    <li><strong>Required Permissions:</strong> admin, developer, or editor roles</li>
    <li><strong>Parameters:</strong>
        <ul>
            <li><code>startup_method</code> (optional): Method to start the server. Default is <code>command</code> (direct execution). Currently supported: <code>command</code></li>
        </ul>
    </li>
    <li><strong>Response:</strong> JSON object with status, message, and timestamp</li>
</ul>

<h3>Auto-Startup on Query Failure</h3>
<p>When a query is sent to the <code>/ai/generate</code> endpoint and the Ollama server is not running on localhost:</p>
<ul>
    <li>The system automatically attempts to start the server using the configured startup method</li>
    <li>After successful startup, the query is automatically retried</li>
    <li>This behavior only applies to localhost connections (remote servers must be manually started)</li>
    <li>If startup fails, an error message is returned to the user</li>
</ul>

<h2>Generate Endpoint</h2>
<p><code>/ai/generate</code> - Sends a prompt to the Ollama AI model for processing.</p>
<ul>
    <li><strong>Method:</strong> POST</li>
    <li><strong>Parameters:</strong>
        <ul>
            <li><code>prompt</code> (required): The user's input prompt</li>
            <li><code>model</code> (optional): AI model to use (default: llama3.1)</li>
            <li><code>host</code> (optional): Ollama server host (default: localhost)</li>
        </ul>
    </li>
    <li><strong>Auto-Startup Feature:</strong> If Ollama is not running on localhost, the server will be automatically started and the query retried</li>
</ul>

<h2>Objectives</h2>
<ul>
    <li>Implement AI-driven recommendations for content management.</li>
    <li>Utilize natural language processing for user queries and interactions.</li>
    <li>Enhance data analysis capabilities for better decision-making.</li>
    <li>Provide automatic server lifecycle management for seamless AI integration.</li>
</ul>

